disclaimer.en: ATVs with engines up to 50cc are recommended for use only by riders 6 years and older and always with adult supervision. ATVs with engines of 70 to 90cc are recommended only for use by riders 12 years and older, and always under adult supervision. ATVs with engines of 90cc or greater are recommended for use only by riders 16 years and older. Our Side-by-Side Vehicles are recommended for use only by riders of 16 years and older. ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles are built to operate within their design limits. Safe towable weights, together with maximum carrying capacity are identified in the owner's manual if applicable. For durability, reliability, but most important of all, operator and passenger (for Side-by-Side Vehicle only) safety, under no circumstances should the recommended capacities be exceeded. ATVs can be hazardous to operate. For your safety: always avoid paved surfaces. ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles are designed for unpaved surfaces only. Riding on paved surfaces may seriously affect handling and control and can cause loss of control. Always wear a helmet, eye protection, and protective clothing. Never carry any passengers on ATVs and always wear a seatbelt when riding a Side-by-Side Vehicle. Never engage stunt riding. Riding and alcohol/drugs dont mix. Avoid excessive speed. And be particularly careful on difficult terrain. Please tread lightly: always ride in a responsible manner, respecting the environment as well as country and local laws. Yamaha recommends that all ATV and Side-by-Side Vehicle riders take an approved training course. For safety and training information, see your dealer or call your Yamaha Distributor in your country. The specification and appearance of Yamaha products will be varied from time to time without notice, and those shown here are for illustrative purposes only and are not contractual descriptions of products. Some models are shown with optional accessories. The riders in this brochure are professionals: don't attempt to emulate them. All ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles come with a 12-month Limited Factory Warranty. See your dealer for details.
disclaimer.frBE: Les quads quips dun moteur allant jusqu 50cm sont uniquement recommands pour les enfants de 6ans minimum et toujours sous la surveillance dun adulte. Les quads quips de moteurs compris entre 70 et 90cm sont uniquement recommands pour les enfants de 12ans minimum et toujours sous la surveillance d'un adulte. Les quads quips d'un moteur de 90cm ou plus sont uniquement recommands pour les adolescents gs de 16ans minimum. Les SSV sont seulement destins  des pilotes gs de 16ans et plus. Les quads et SSV sont conus pour fonctionner dans la limite de leurs capacits. Les poids de traction et de charge maximum autoriss sont indiqus dans le manuel de l'utilisateur. Pour une meilleure durabilit et fiabilit du produit, mais surtout pour des raisons de scurit (pour les SSV seulement), les capacits de charge recommandes ne doivent en aucun cas tre dpasses. Les quads peuvent tre dangereux  manipuler. Pour votre scurit: vitez toujours les surfaces goudronnes. Les quads et SSV sont conus pour rouler uniquement sur les surfaces non goudronnes. La conduite sur surfaces goudronnes peut gravement affecter la maniabilit et provoquer une perte de contrle du vhicule. Portez toujours un casque, des lunettes et un quipement adquat. Ne transportez jamais de passagers sur un quad, et portez toujours une ceinture de scurit sur un SSV. Neffectuez jamais dacrobaties. La conduite et lalcool ou les drogues ne font pas bon mnage. Conduisez  une vitesse raisonnable. Soyez particulirement prudent sur les terrains difficiles. Attention: pilotez toujours de manire responsable, en respectant lenvironnement ainsi que les lgislations locales et nationales. Yamaha recommande vivement  tous les pilotes de quads et de SSV de suivre des stages de formation auprs de professionnels agrs. Pour plus d'informations concernant la scurit et les stages, contactez votre concessionnaire ou le distributeur Yamaha de votre pays. Les caractristiques et les coloris des produits Yamaha sont rgulirement modifis sans notification pralable. Les produits illustrs ici ne sont prsents qu' titre indicatif et ne font pas l'objet d'une description contractuelle. Certains modles sont prsents avec des accessoires disponibles en option. Les photos ont t ralises avec des pilotes professionnels: nessayez pas de les imiter. Tous les quads et SSV sont vendus avec une garantie usine limite de 12mois. Veuillez contacter votre concessionnaire pour plus dinformations.
disclaimer.deCH: ATVs mit bis zu 50ccm Hubraum sollten nur von Fahrern ab 6Jahren und unter Aufsicht eines Erwachsenen gefahren werden. ATVs mit Motoren von 70 bis 90ccm Hubraum sollten nur von Fahrern ab 12Jahren und unter Aufsicht eines Erwachsenen bewegt werden. ATVs mit mehr als 90ccm Hubraum sollten nur von Fahrern ab 16Jahren gefahren werden. Unsere Side-by-Side-Fahrzeuge sollten nur von Fahrern ab 16Jahren gefahren werden. Beim Betrieb der ATVs und Side-by-Side-Fahrzeuge von Yamaha mssen die konstruktionsbedingten Grenzen beachtet werden. Die zulssige Anhngelast sowie die maximale Zuladung sind ggf. im Benutzerhandbuch angegeben. Im Interesse der Funktionsfhigkeit, der Zuverlssigkeit und insbesondere der Sicherheit von Fahrer und Beifahrer (nur fr Side-by-Side-Fahrzeuge) drfen die angegebenen Werte unter keinen Umstnden berschritten werden. Der Betrieb eines ATV kann gefhrlich sein. Fr deine Sicherheit: Meide stets asphaltierte Strassen. ATVs und Side-by-Side-Fahrzeuge sind nur fr den Betrieb auf unbefestigten Strassen konzipiert. Das Fahren auf befestigten Strassen kann die Handlingeigenschaften wesentlich beeintrchtigen und zum Verlust der Fahrzeugkontrolle fhren. Tragen stets einen Helm, Augenschutz sowie Sicherheitsbekleidung. Nimm auf ATVs nie einen Beifahrer mit und trage immer den Sitzgurt, wenn du ein Side-by-Side-Fahrzeug fhrst. Versuche dich nicht als Stunt-Fahrer. Fahre niemals unter dem Einfluss von Alkohol bzw. Drogen. Vermeide zu hohe Geschwindigkeiten. Fahre im schwierigen Gelnde besonders vorsichtig. Bitte nehmen Sie Rcksicht: Fahre verantwortungsbewusst, schone die Umwelt und beachte die gesetzlichen und rtlichen Bestimmungen. Yamaha empfiehlt allen ATV und Side-by-Side-Fahrzeug-Fahrern einen entsprechenden Fahrerlehrgang. Weitere Informationen zu Sicherheits- und Trainingsveranstaltungen erhltst du von deiner Yamaha Vertretung. Yamaha behlt sich das Recht vor, technische Daten, Ausstattungsmerkmale und Farben seiner Produkte ohne vorherige Ankndigung zu ndern; die hier gezeigten Abbildungen dienen daher nur zu Anschauungszwecken und stellen keine zugesicherten Eigenschaften dar. Einige der abgebildeten Modelle sind mit Sonderzubehr ausgestattet. Die Fahrer in dieser Broschre sind Experten: Versuche nicht, sie nachzuahmen. Yamaha gewhrt auf alle ATVs und Side-by-Side-Fahrzeuge eine Werksgarantie von 12Monaten. Weitere Informationen erhltst du von deinem autorisierten Yamaha Vertragshndler.

disclaimer.nlNL: ATV's met motoren tot 50cc worden alleen aanbevolen voor gebruik door rijders van 6 jaar en ouder en altijd onder toezicht van een volwassene. ATV's met motoren van 70 tot 90cc worden alleen aanbevolen voor gebruik door rijders van 12jaar en ouder en altijd onder toezicht van een volwassene. ATV's met motoren van 90cc of meer worden alleen aanbevolen voor gebruik door rijders van 16jaar en ouder. Onze Side-by-Side voertuigen worden alleen aanbevolen voor gebruik door rijders van 16 jaar en ouder. ATV's en Side-by-Side voertuigen zijn gebouwd om binnen hun ontwerplimieten te functioneren. Informatie over de veilige trekgewichten en het maximale laadvermogen is, waar van toepassing, te vinden in de gebruikershandleiding. Met het oog op duurzaamheid en betrouwbaarheid, maar vooral vanwege de veiligheid van de berijder en de passagier (alleen voor Side-by-Side voertuigen), mogen de aanbevolen waarden nooit worden overschreden. ATV's dienen uiterst zorgvuldig gebruikt te worden. Voor jouw veiligheid: Vermijd altijd verharde oppervlakken. ATV's en Side-by-Side-voertuigen zijn alleen ontworpen voor onverharde oppervlakken. Rijden op verharde ondergrond kan het rijgedrag negatief benvloeden en kan leiden tot verlies van controle over het voertuig. Draag altijd een helm, oogbescherming en beschermende rijkleding. Vervoer nooit passagiers op ATV's en draag altijd een veiligheidsgordel wanneer je een Side-by-Side-voertuig bestuurt. Probeer geen stunts uit te halen. Rijden en gebruik van alcohol, drugs of medicijnen gaan niet samen. Vermijd te hoge snelheid. En wees vooral voorzichtig op moeilijk terrein. Neem je verantwoordelijkheid: rij altijd op verantwoordelijke wijze, met respect voor het milieu en met inachtneming van nationale en lokale wet- en regelgeving. Yamaha adviseert alle berijders van ATV en Side-by-Side-voertuigen een erkende rijvaardigheidstraining te volgen. Meer informatie over veiligheid en rijvaardigheidstrainingen kun je krijgen bij jouw Yamaha ATV-dealer. De specificaties en het uiterlijk van Yamaha-producten kunnen nu en dan zonder voorafgaande kennisgeving worden gewijzigd en maken geen deel uit van een contractuele productbeschrijving. De producten zijn hier uitsluitend ter illustratie weergegeven. Sommige modellen zijn afgebeeld met optionele accessoires. De bestuurders in deze brochure zijn professionals: probeer ze niet na te doen. Alle ATV's en Side-by-Side voertuigen worden geleverd met een beperkte fabrieksgarantie van 12 maanden. disclaimer.itIT:
Si raccomanda l'uso degli ATV con motori fino a 50 cc solo ai piloti dai 6 anni in su e sempre sotto la supervisione di un adulto. Si raccomanda l'uso degli ATV con motori dai 70 ai 90 cc solo ai piloti dai 12 anni in su e sempre sotto la supervisione di un adulto. Si raccomanda l'uso degli ATV con motori da 90 cc o superiori solo ai piloti dai 16 anni in su. Si raccomanda l'uso dei nostri Side by Side solo ai piloti dai 16 anni in su. Gli ATV e i Side by Side Yamaha sono realizzati per funzionare entro i limiti definiti dal progetto. I pesi di traino sicuri e la massima capacit di carico, ove applicabili, sono indicati nel manuale d'uso. Per garantire la durata e laffidabilit del veicolo, ma soprattutto lincolumit del pilota e del passeggero (solo per i mezzi Side by Side),  necessario non superare mai, per nessun motivo, la capacit di carico indicata. Gli ATV possono essere pericolosi. Per la tua sicurezza: evita sempre le strade asfaltate. I nostri ATV e Side by Side sono progettati per i percorsi non asfaltati. Guidarli sullasfalto pu condizionare negativamente la maneggevolezza e il controllo del mezzo, causando notevoli difficolt. Indossa sempre casco, occhiali e abbigliamento protettivo. Raccomandiamo di non portare passeggeri sugli ATV e di indossare sempre la cintura sul Side by Side. Evita le acrobazie. Non consumare alcol o droga prima e durante la guida. Evita le velocit eccessive. Presta particolare attenzione sui terreni difficili. Presta attenzione alla tua guida: guida sempre in modo responsabile, rispettando lambiente, la natura e le leggi locali. Yamaha consiglia a tutti i piloti di ATV e Side by Side di seguire un corso di guida autorizzato. Per ulteriori informazioni sulla sicurezza e sui corsi di guida, contatta il tuo concessionario Yamaha di zona.

disclaimer.ptPT: Recomenda-se que os Moto 4 com motores at 50 cc de cilindrada sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelos menos 6 anos de idade e sempre sob a superviso de um adulto. Finalmente, recomenda-se que os Moto 4 com motores com mais de 90 cc de cilindrada sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelo menos 16 anos de idade. Recomenda-se que os nossos veculos Side-by-Side sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelo menos 16 anos de idade. A conduo em superfcies pavimentadas poder afetar gravemente a manobrabilidade e provocar a perda do controlo. Use sempre capacete, proteo para os olhos e vesturio apropriado. Se tiver ingerido lcool ou tomado medicamentos que possam comprometer a sua ateno ou os seus reflexos, no conduza. Evite conduzir a uma velocidade excessiva. Seja consciente: conduza sempre de uma forma responsvel, respeitando o ambiente, a legislao nacional e os regulamentos locais. disclaimer.en: ATVs with engines up to 50cc are recommended for use only by riders 6 years and older and always with adult supervision. ATVs with engines of 70 to 90cc are recommended only for use by riders 12 years and older, and always under adult supervision. ATVs with engines of 90cc or greater are recommended for use only by riders 16 years and older. Our Side-by-Side Vehicles are recommended for use only by riders of 16 years and older. ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles are built to operate within their design limits. Safe towable weights, together with maximum carrying capacity are identified in the owner's manual if applicable. For durability, reliability, but most important of all, operator and passenger (for Side-by-Side Vehicle only) safety, under no circumstances should the recommended capacities be exceeded. ATVs can be hazardous to operate. For your safety: always avoid paved surfaces. ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles are designed for unpaved surfaces only. Riding on paved surfaces may seriously affect handling and control and can cause loss of control. Always wear a helmet, eye protection, and protective clothing. Never carry any passengers on ATVs and always wear a seatbelt when riding a Side-by-Side Vehicle. Never engage stunt riding. Riding and alcohol/drugs dont mix. Avoid excessive speed. And be particularly careful on difficult terrain. Please tread lightly: always ride in a responsible manner, respecting the environment as well as country and local laws. Yamaha recommends that all ATV and Side-by-Side Vehicle riders take an approved training course. For safety and training information, see your dealer or call your Yamaha Distributor in your country. The specification and appearance of Yamaha products will be varied from time to time without notice, and those shown here are for illustrative purposes only and are not contractual descriptions of products. Some models are shown with optional accessories. The riders in this brochure are professionals: don't attempt to emulate them. All ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles come with a 12-month Limited Factory Warranty. See your dealer for details.
disclaimer.frBE: Les quads quips dun moteur allant jusqu 50cm sont uniquement recommands pour les enfants de 6ans minimum et toujours sous la surveillance dun adulte. Les quads quips de moteurs compris entre 70 et 90cm sont uniquement recommands pour les enfants de 12ans minimum et toujours sous la surveillance d'un adulte. Les quads quips d'un moteur de 90cm ou plus sont uniquement recommands pour les adolescents gs de 16ans minimum. Les SSV sont seulement destins  des pilotes gs de 16ans et plus. Les quads et SSV sont conus pour fonctionner dans la limite de leurs capacits. Les poids de traction et de charge maximum autoriss sont indiqus dans le manuel de l'utilisateur. Pour une meilleure durabilit et fiabilit du produit, mais surtout pour des raisons de scurit (pour les SSV seulement), les capacits de charge recommandes ne doivent en aucun cas tre dpasses. Les quads peuvent tre dangereux  manipuler. Pour votre scurit: vitez toujours les surfaces goudronnes. Les quads et SSV sont conus pour rouler uniquement sur les surfaces non goudronnes. La conduite sur surfaces goudronnes peut gravement affecter la maniabilit et provoquer une perte de contrle du vhicule. Portez toujours un casque, des lunettes et un quipement adquat. Ne transportez jamais de passagers sur un quad, et portez toujours une ceinture de scurit sur un SSV. Neffectuez jamais dacrobaties. La conduite et lalcool ou les drogues ne font pas bon mnage. Conduisez  une vitesse raisonnable. Soyez particulirement prudent sur les terrains difficiles. Attention: pilotez toujours de manire responsable, en respectant lenvironnement ainsi que les lgislations locales et nationales. Yamaha recommande vivement  tous les pilotes de quads et de SSV de suivre des stages de formation auprs de professionnels agrs. Pour plus d'informations concernant la scurit et les stages, contactez votre concessionnaire ou le distributeur Yamaha de votre pays. Les caractristiques et les coloris des produits Yamaha sont rgulirement modifis sans notification pralable. Les produits illustrs ici ne sont prsents qu' titre indicatif et ne font pas l'objet d'une description contractuelle. Certains modles sont prsents avec des accessoires disponibles en option. Les photos ont t ralises avec des pilotes professionnels: nessayez pas de les imiter. Tous les quads et SSV sont vendus avec une garantie usine limite de 12mois. Veuillez contacter votre concessionnaire pour plus dinformations.
disclaimer.deCH: ATVs mit bis zu 50ccm Hubraum sollten nur von Fahrern ab 6Jahren und unter Aufsicht eines Erwachsenen gefahren werden. ATVs mit Motoren von 70 bis 90ccm Hubraum sollten nur von Fahrern ab 12Jahren und unter Aufsicht eines Erwachsenen bewegt werden. ATVs mit mehr als 90ccm Hubraum sollten nur von Fahrern ab 16Jahren gefahren werden. Unsere Side-by-Side-Fahrzeuge sollten nur von Fahrern ab 16Jahren gefahren werden. Beim Betrieb der ATVs und Side-by-Side-Fahrzeuge von Yamaha mssen die konstruktionsbedingten Grenzen beachtet werden. Die zulssige Anhngelast sowie die maximale Zuladung sind ggf. im Benutzerhandbuch angegeben. Im Interesse der Funktionsfhigkeit, der Zuverlssigkeit und insbesondere der Sicherheit von Fahrer und Beifahrer (nur fr Side-by-Side-Fahrzeuge) drfen die angegebenen Werte unter keinen Umstnden berschritten werden. disclaimer.ptPT: Recomenda-se que os Moto 4 com motores at 50 cc de cilindrada sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelos menos 6 anos de idade e sempre sob a superviso de um adulto. Da mesma forma, recomenda-se que os Moto 4 com motores entre 70 e 90 cc de cilindrada sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelo menos 12 anos de idade e sempre sob a superviso de um adulto. Finalmente, recomenda-se que os Moto 4 com motores com mais de 90 cc de cilindrada sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelo menos 16 anos de idade. Recomenda-se que os nossos veculos Side-by-Side sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelo menos 16 anos de idade. Os Moto 4 e veculos Side-by-Side destinam-se a ser utilizados dentro dos limites do respetivo design. Caso se aplique, os valores de reboque de cargas em segurana e da capacidade mxima de carga encontram-se no manual do proprietrio. Por questes de durabilidade, fiabilidade e, acima de tudo, segurana do condutor e do passageiro (apenas para veculos Side-by-Side), as capacidades recomendadas no devem, em circunstncia alguma, ser excedidas. A conduo de um Moto 4 pode ser perigosa. Para sua segurana: evite sempre superfcies pavimentadas. Os Moto 4 e veculos Side-by-Side foram concebidos para serem utilizados exclusivamente em superfcies no pavimentadas. A conduo em superfcies pavimentadas poder afetar gravemente a manobrabilidade e provocar a perda do controlo. Use sempre capacete, proteo para os olhos e vesturio apropriado. Nunca transporte passageiros em veculos Moto 4 e utilize sempre o cinto de segurana em veculos Side-by-Side. Nunca tente fazer habilidades. Se tiver ingerido lcool ou tomado medicamentos que possam comprometer a sua ateno ou os seus reflexos, no conduza. Evite conduzir a uma velocidade excessiva. Da mesma forma, conduza de forma especialmente cuidadosa em terrenos difceis. Seja consciente: conduza sempre de uma forma responsvel, respeitando o ambiente, a legislao nacional e os regulamentos locais. A Yamaha recomenda a todos os condutores de Moto 4 e veculos Side-by-Side a frequncia de um curso de formao certificado. Para obter informaes relativas a segurana e formao, consulte o seu concessionrio ou o distribuidor Yamaha nacional. As especificaes e o aspeto dos produtos Yamaha podem sofrer periodicamente alteraes sem aviso prvio; as especificaes e as imagens includas neste documento destinam-se a fins meramente ilustrativos, no constituindo descries contratuais dos produtos. Alguns modelos so apresentados com acessrios opcionais. Os condutores presentes neste catlogo so profissionais: no tente imit-los. Todos os Moto 4 e veculos Side-by-Side so fornecidos com uma garantia de fbrica limitada de 12 meses. Para mais informaes, consulte o seu concessionrio.
disclaimer.roRO: ATV-urile cu motor pn la 50 cmc sunt recomandate numai pentru piloi cu vrsta de minimum 6 ani i numai sub supravegherea unui adult. ATV-urile cu o capacitate a motorului de la 70 pn la 90 cmc sunt recomandate numai pentru piloi cu vrsta de minimum 12 ani i numai sub supravegherea unui adult. ATV-urile cu o capacitate a motorului de 90 cmc sau mai mare sunt recomandate numai pentru piloi cu vrsta de minimum 16 ani. Greutile tractabile sigure, mpreun cu capacitatea de transport maxim, sunt detaliate n manualul de utilizare, dac este cazul. Pentru durabilitate i fiabilitate, dar mai ales pentru sigurana operatorului i a pasagerilor (doar pentru vehiculele side-by-side), n niciun caz nu se vor depi capacitile recomandate. Utilizarea ATV-urilor poate fi periculoas. Pentru sigurana ta: evit ntotdeauna suprafeele pavate. ATV-urile i vehiculele side-by-side sunt destinate numai suprafeelor nepavate. Pilotarea pe suprafee pavate poate afecta grav manevrarea i controlul ATV-ului i poate conduce la pierderea controlului asupra acestuia. Poart ntotdeauna casc, ochelari i echipament de protecie. Nu transporta niciodat pasageri pe ATV-uri i poart ntotdeauna centura de siguran atunci cnd cltoreti cu un vehicul side-by-side. Nu te angaja niciodat n cascadorii. Pilotarea i alcoolul/medicamentele nu sunt compatibile. Evit viteza excesiv. Fii deosebit de atent pe teren accidentat. Ruleaz cu atenie: piloteaz ntotdeauna n mod responsabil, respectnd mediul nconjurtor, precum i legislaia naional i local. Yamaha recomand ca toi conductorii de ATV-uri i vehicule side-by-side s urmeze un curs de instruire aprobat. Las especificaciones y la apariencia de los productos Yamaha pueden variar sin previo aviso. Los que se muestran aqu tienen fines puramente ilustrativos y no implican una descripcin contractual de los productos. Algunos modelos se muestran con accesorios opcionales. disclaimer.en: ATVs with engines up to 50cc are recommended for use only by riders 6 years and older and always with adult supervision. ATVs with engines of 70 to 90cc are recommended only for use by riders 12 years and older, and always under adult supervision. ATVs with engines of 90cc or greater are recommended for use only by riders 16 years and older. Our Side-by-Side Vehicles are recommended for use only by riders of 16 years and older. ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles are built to operate within their design limits. Safe towable weights, together with maximum carrying capacity are identified in the owner's manual if applicable. For durability, reliability, but most important of all, operator and passenger (for Side-by-Side Vehicle only) safety, under no circumstances should the recommended capacities be exceeded. ATVs can be hazardous to operate. For your safety: always avoid paved surfaces. ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles are designed for unpaved surfaces only. Riding on paved surfaces may seriously affect handling and control and can cause loss of control. Always wear a helmet, eye protection, and protective clothing. Never carry any passengers on ATVs and always wear a seatbelt when riding a Side-by-Side Vehicle. Never engage stunt riding. Riding and alcohol/drugs dont mix. Avoid excessive speed. And be particularly careful on difficult terrain. Please tread lightly: always ride in a responsible manner, respecting the environment as well as country and local laws. Yamaha recommends that all ATV and Side-by-Side Vehicle riders take an approved training course. For safety and training information, see your dealer or call your Yamaha Distributor in your country. The specification and appearance of Yamaha products will be varied from time to time without notice, and those shown here are for illustrative purposes only and are not contractual descriptions of products. Some models are shown with optional accessories. The riders in this brochure are professionals: don't attempt to emulate them. All ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles come with a 12-month Limited Factory Warranty. See your dealer for details.

Si raccomanda l'uso degli ATV con motori dai 70 ai 90 cc solo ai piloti dai 12 anni in su e sempre sotto la supervisione di un adulto. Si raccomanda l'uso degli ATV con motori da 90 cc o superiori solo ai piloti dai 16 anni in su. Si raccomanda l'uso dei nostri Side by Side solo ai piloti dai 16 anni in su. Gli ATV e i Side by Side Yamaha sono realizzati per funzionare entro i limiti definiti dal progetto. I pesi di traino sicuri e la massima capacit di carico, ove applicabili, sono indicati nel manuale d'uso. Per garantire la durata e laffidabilit del veicolo, ma soprattutto lincolumit del pilota e del passeggero (solo per i mezzi Side by Side),  necessario non superare mai, per nessun motivo, la capacit di carico indicata. Gli ATV possono essere pericolosi. Per la tua sicurezza: evita sempre le strade asfaltate. I nostri ATV e Side by Side sono progettati per i percorsi non asfaltati. Guidarli sullasfalto pu condizionare negativamente la maneggevolezza e il controllo del mezzo, causando notevoli difficolt. Indossa sempre casco, occhiali e abbigliamento protettivo. Raccomandiamo di non portare passeggeri sugli ATV e di indossare sempre la cintura sul Side by Side. Evita le acrobazie. Non consumare alcol o droga prima e durante la guida. Evita le velocit eccessive. Presta particolare attenzione sui terreni difficili. Presta attenzione alla tua guida: guida sempre in modo responsabile, rispettando lambiente, la natura e le leggi locali. Yamaha consiglia a tutti i piloti di ATV e Side by Side di seguire un corso di guida autorizzato. Per ulteriori informazioni sulla sicurezza e sui corsi di guida, contatta il tuo concessionario Yamaha di zona.

disclaimer.en: ATVs with engines up to 50cc are recommended for use only by riders 6 years and older and always with adult supervision. ATVs with engines of 70 to 90cc are recommended only for use by riders 12 years and older, and always under adult supervision. ATVs with engines of 90cc or greater are recommended for use only by riders 16 years and older. Our Side-by-Side Vehicles are recommended for use only by riders of 16 years and older. ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles are built to operate within their design limits. Safe towable weights, together with maximum carrying capacity are identified in the owner's manual if applicable. For durability, reliability, but most important of all, operator and passenger (for Side-by-Side Vehicle only) safety, under no circumstances should the recommended capacities be exceeded. ATVs can be hazardous to operate. For your safety: always avoid paved surfaces. ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles are designed for unpaved surfaces only. Riding on paved surfaces may seriously affect handling and control and can cause loss of control. Always wear a helmet, eye protection, and protective clothing. Never carry any passengers on ATVs and always wear a seatbelt when riding a Side-by-Side Vehicle. Never engage stunt riding. Riding and alcohol/drugs dont mix. Avoid excessive speed. And be particularly careful on difficult terrain. Please tread lightly: always ride in a responsible manner, respecting the environment as well as country and local laws. Yamaha recommends that all ATV and Side-by-Side Vehicle riders take an approved training course. For safety and training information, see your dealer or call your Yamaha Distributor in your country. The specification and appearance of Yamaha products will be varied from time to time without notice, and those shown here are for illustrative purposes only and are not contractual descriptions of products. Some models are shown with optional accessories. The riders in this brochure are professionals: don't attempt to emulate them. All ATVs and Side-by-Side Vehicles come with a 12-month Limited Factory Warranty. See your dealer for details.

Si raccomanda l'uso degli ATV con motori da 90 cc o superiori solo ai piloti dai 16 anni in su. Si raccomanda l'uso dei nostri Side by Side solo ai piloti dai 16 anni in su. Gli ATV e i Side by Side Yamaha sono realizzati per funzionare entro i limiti definiti dal progetto. I pesi di traino sicuri e la massima capacit di carico, ove applicabili, sono indicati nel manuale d'uso. Per garantire la durata e laffidabilit del veicolo, ma soprattutto lincolumit del pilota e del passeggero (solo per i mezzi Side by Side),  necessario non superare mai, per nessun motivo, la capacit di carico indicata. Gli ATV possono essere pericolosi. Per la tua sicurezza: evita sempre le strade asfaltate. I nostri ATV e Side by Side sono progettati per i percorsi non asfaltati. Guidarli sullasfalto pu condizionare negativamente la maneggevolezza e il controllo del mezzo, causando notevoli difficolt. Indossa sempre casco, occhiali e abbigliamento protettivo. Raccomandiamo di non portare passeggeri sugli ATV e di indossare sempre la cintura sul Side by Side. Evita le acrobazie. Non consumare alcol o droga prima e durante la guida. Evita le velocit eccessive. Presta particolare attenzione sui terreni difficili. Presta attenzione alla tua guida: guida sempre in modo responsabile, rispettando lambiente, la natura e le leggi locali. Yamaha consiglia a tutti i piloti di ATV e Side by Side di seguire un corso di guida autorizzato. Per ulteriori informazioni sulla sicurezza e sui corsi di guida, contatta il tuo concessionario Yamaha di zona.

disclaimer.ptPT: Recomenda-se que os Moto 4 com motores at 50 cc de cilindrada sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelos menos 6 anos de idade e sempre sob a superviso de um adulto. Da mesma forma, recomenda-se que os Moto 4 com motores entre 70 e 90 cc de cilindrada sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelo menos 12 anos de idade e sempre sob a superviso de um adulto. Finalmente, recomenda-se que os Moto 4 com motores com mais de 90 cc de cilindrada sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelo menos 16 anos de idade. Recomenda-se que os nossos veculos Side-by-Side sejam utilizados exclusivamente por condutores com pelo menos 16 anos de idade. Os Moto 4 e veculos Side-by-Side destinam-se a ser utilizados dentro dos limites do respetivo design. Caso se aplique, os valores de reboque de cargas em segurana e da capacidade mxima de carga encontram-se no manual do proprietrio. Por questes de durabilidade, fiabilidade e, acima de tudo, segurana do condutor e do passageiro (apenas para veculos Side-by-Side), as capacidades recomendadas no devem, em circunstncia alguma, ser excedidas. A conduo de um Moto 4 pode ser perigosa. Para sua segurana: evite sempre superfcies pavimentadas. Os Moto 4 e veculos Side-by-Side foram concebidos para serem utilizados exclusivamente em superfcies no pavimentadas. A conduo em superfcies pavimentadas poder afetar gravemente a manobrabilidade e provocar a perda do controlo. Use sempre capacete, proteo para os olhos e vesturio apropriado. Nunca transporte passageiros em veculos Moto 4 e utilize sempre o cinto de segurana em veculos Side-by-Side. Nunca tente fazer habilidades. Se tiver ingerido lcool ou tomado medicamentos que possam comprometer a sua ateno ou os seus reflexos, no conduza. Evite conduzir a uma velocidade excessiva. Da mesma forma, conduza de forma especialmente cuidadosa em terrenos difceis. Seja consciente: conduza sempre de uma forma responsvel, respeitando o ambiente, a legislao nacional e os regulamentos locais. A Yamaha recomenda a todos os condutores de Moto 4 e veculos Side-by-Side a frequncia de um curso de formao certificado. Para obter informaes relativas a segurana e formao, consulte o seu concessionrio ou o distribuidor Yamaha nacional. As especificaes e o aspeto dos produtos Yamaha podem sofrer periodicamente alteraes sem aviso prvio; as especificaes e as imagens includas neste documento destinam-se a fins meramente ilustrativos, no constituindo descries contratuais dos produtos. Alguns modelos so apresentados com acessrios opcionais. Os condutores presentes neste catlogo so profissionais: no tente imit-los. Todos os Moto 4 e veculos Side-by-Side so fornecidos com uma garantia de fbrica limitada de 12 meses. Para mais informaes, consulte o seu concessionrio.

Vonjo ATV-jev z agregati z 90 cm3 ali ve priporoamo samo za voznike od 16 let naprej. Uporabo naih tirikolesnikov "Side-by-Side" priporoamo samo voznikom, starim 16 let ali ve. ATV-ji in "Side-by-Side" vozila so zasnovani tako, da delujejo znotraj meja svojih zmogljivosti. Dovoljene vlene tee so skupaj z najvejo nosilnostjo navedene v navodilih za uporabo in vzdrevanje (odvisno od modela). Priporoenih kapacitet ne smete prekoraiti, saj s tem zagotovite trpenost in zanesljivost vozila ter poskrbite za varnost voznika in sopotnikov (le za "Side-by-Side" vozila). Upravljanje ATV-jev je lahko nevarno. Za vao varnost: Vedno se izogibajte tlakovanih povrin. Modeli ATV in "Side-by-Side" so namenjeni samo za terensko uporabo. Vonja po tlakovanih povrinah lahko mono vpliva na upravljanje in tako povzroi izgubo nadzora. Vedno nosite elado, zaito za oi in zaitno obleko. Nikoli ne prevaajte potnikov na vozilu ATV in med vonjo z vozilom "Side-by-Side" bodite vedno pripasani. Med vonjo nikoli ne izvajajte akrobacij. Kadar vozite, nikoli ne uivajte alkohola ali zdravil. Izogibajte se prekomernim hitrostim. Bodite e posebej previdni na zahtevnem terenu. Prosimo vozite poasi: Vedno vozite na odgovoren nain, spotujte okolje kot tudi dravne in lokalne zakone. Yamaha priporoa, da se vsi vozniki ATV-jev in vozil "Side-by-Side" udeleijo ustreznega usposabljanja. Za informacije o varnosti in usposabljanju se obrnite na svojega prodajalca ali pokliite Yamahinega distributerja v svoji dravi. Specifikacije in videz Yamahinih proizvodov se lahko obasno spremenijo brez predhodnega obvestila. Prikazane slike sluijo samo za ponazoritev in niso dejanski pogodbeni opisi izdelkov. Nekateri modeli so prikazani z izbirno dodatno opremo. Vozniki v tej brouri so profesionalci: ne poskuajte jih posnemati. Vsi modeli STV in "Side-by-Side" imajo 12-meseno omejeno tovarniko garancijo. Za podrobnosti se obrnite na svojega prodajalca.
